(nDCacheTLBWays, CPI).explanation: Increasing the number of ways in the data cache TLB reduces TLB miss rates and memory access latency, which directly decreases the cycles per instruction by improving memory system performance;

(nDCacheTLBWays, DCacheMiss).explanation: Higher associativity in the data cache TLB reduces TLB conflicts and improves virtual-to-physical address translation efficiency, which can reduce data cache miss rates by enabling more effective memory access patterns;
